        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 6:12PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 611 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles southwest of Augusta, or 42 miles southwest of Choteau, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Augusta and Nilan Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
